@startuml 00_System_Overview
!theme plain
title 3D Data Quality Framework  |  System Overview

skinparam backgroundColor #FAFAFA
skinparam linetype ortho
skinparam defaultFontName Arial
skinparam defaultFontSize 11

skinparam rectangle {
  RoundCorner 12
  BorderColor #90A4AE
  FontSize 11
}
skinparam database {
  BackgroundColor #E3F2FD
  BorderColor #1565C0
  FontSize 10
}
skinparam arrow {
  Color #546E7A
  FontSize 9
  Thickness 1.5
}
skinparam package {
  BorderColor #B0BEC5
  BackgroundColor #FFFFFF
  FontSize 10
}

top to bottom direction

' ==================================================
' ROW 0 -- USERS
' ==================================================

rectangle "Stakeholders" as USERS #FFF3E0 {
  actor "Data Engineers  |  Business Analysts  |  Product Owners  |  Tech Leads  |  DataOps  |  Data Governance" as USR
}

' ==================================================
' ROW 1 -- SELF-SERVICE RULE CAPTURE
' ==================================================

rectangle "Self-Service Rule Capture  (DQ Chatbot App + DQ Backend App)" as CAPTURE #E8F5E9 {

  rectangle "DQ Chatbot App\n(Databricks Apps + LangGraph)\nNL Q&A  |  Rule proposal\nCoverage gaps  |  KPI lookup" as GENIE #C5CAE9

  rectangle "Rule Authoring Pipeline\n(DQ Backend App)\nRAG Retriever  >  SQL Generator  >  Security Guard\nSQL Validator  >  Duplicate Detector  >  Trend Scorer\nRule Submitter  >  Approval Gateway\nCheck Suggestion Resolver (cache + schema gate)" as AUTHORING #C8E6C9

  rectangle "LLM Engine\n(Model Serving Endpoint)\nIntent classification\nSQL generation\nTrend scoring" as LLM #DCEDC8
}

' ==================================================
' ROW 2 -- SHARED KNOWLEDGE + STORAGE
' ==================================================

rectangle "RAG Knowledge Base\n(Databricks Vector Search + UC Volumes)\ndata_contracts/  |  supported_checks/\nsql_patterns/  |  examples/  |  domain_glossary/" as RAG #EDE7F6

rectangle "Rule & Metric Store  (Unity Catalog -- Delta Tables)" as STORE #E3F2FD {
  database "anomaly_check_config\n(Rule Registry)" as RuleDB
  database "check_suggestions_cache\n(table_fqn + schema_version)" as SuggestCache
  database "table_daily_metrics\n(Baselines + EWMA)" as MetricsDB
  database "DIGITAL_DATA_ANOMALIES\n(Anomaly Events)" as AnomDB
  database "check_execution_log\n(Run History)" as ExecLog
}

' ==================================================
' ROW 3 -- DRE 3D EXECUTION FRAMEWORK
' ==================================================

rectangle "DRE 3D Execution Framework  (Databricks Workflows + Apps)" as DRE #E3F2FD {

  rectangle "D1  DETECTION\n(Anomaly Detection Engine)\nProfiler  |  Baseline Learner\nCheck Dispatcher (9 paths)\nAlert Manager\n[KPI: DRRI]" as D1 #FFCDD2

  rectangle "D2  DIAGNOSIS\nDrift Classifier  |  Lineage Tracer\nSegment Slicer  |  Evidence Retriever\nPlaybook Compiler  |  Prescription Router\nEvidence: job logs / DESCRIBE HISTORY /\nrunbooks (Confluence+UC) / GitHub / ITSM\n[Output: JSON execution recipe]" as D2 #F8BBD0

  rectangle "D3  DEFLECTION\nState Validator  |  Circuit Breaker\nApproval Gate  |  Domain Executors (x12)\nadiClub / CRM / Clickstream / DTC Sales\nPayments / Trading / Metadata / NPS ...\n[Output: Fix + verify + feedback to D1]" as D3 #EDE7F6
}

' ==================================================
' ROW 4 -- NOTIFICATIONS + OUTCOMES
' ==================================================

rectangle "Notifications\n(Email  |  Jira  |  Databricks In-App)" as NOTIF #FFF9C4

rectangle "Business Outcomes\nDRRI > 95%  |  MTTD 48h -> 4-8h\nSLA 60% -> 88%  |  40% toil reduction\n3,032 tables  |  11% -> 90%+ coverage" as OUTCOMES #E8F5E9

' ==================================================
' HIDDEN LAYOUT ANCHORS
' ==================================================

USERS    -[hidden]down-> CAPTURE
CAPTURE  -[hidden]down-> RAG
CAPTURE  -[hidden]down-> STORE
RAG      -[hidden]right-> STORE
STORE    -[hidden]down-> DRE
DRE      -[hidden]down-> NOTIF
DRE      -[hidden]down-> OUTCOMES
NOTIF    -[hidden]right-> OUTCOMES

' ==================================================
' FLOWS
' ==================================================

USR       -down->   GENIE     : Natural language request / Q&A
GENIE     -right->  AUTHORING : LangGraph tool call (WRITE / suggest intent)
AUTHORING -right->  LLM       : SQL generation + scoring

AUTHORING -down->   RAG       : embed_and_search (BGE-M3, top-k=8)
AUTHORING -down->   SuggestCache : cache lookup / upsert
AUTHORING -down->   RuleDB    : INSERT approved rule
AUTHORING -down->   ExecLog   : audit record

RuleDB    -down->   D1        : read active configs
MetricsDB -down->   D1        : load EWMA baselines
D1        -down->   AnomDB    : write anomaly event (PENDING)
D1        -down->   ExecLog   : PASS / FAIL / ERROR / TIMEOUT
D1        -right->  D2
D2        -right->  D3
D3        -down->   MetricsDB : update EWMA baselines
D3        -down->   NOTIF     : violation alerts / approval requests
D1        ..>       NOTIF     : alert on breach
ExecLog   ..>       OUTCOMES  : KPI feed (DRRI, MTTD, SLA %)

note as OverviewGuide
  <b>How to read this diagram</b>
  ---------------------------------------------------------
  <b>TOP ROW</b> -- Who interacts:
  Data Engineers and BAs author rules via the DQ Chatbot App (Databricks Apps + LangGraph).
  Product Owners and Tech Leads approve. DataOps monitors.

  <b>CAPTURE LAYER</b> -- How rules are created:
  NL request -> LLM intent parse -> CRAG-gated RAG retrieval
  (BGE-M3 embeddings, top-k=8, confidence gate)
  -> SQL generation -> Security Guard -> Validator
  -> Duplicate Detector -> Trend Score -> Approval Gateway.
  Result: a governed, versioned rule in anomaly_check_config.

  <b>DETECTION (D1)</b> -- How anomalies are found:
  ANOMALY_DETECTION_JOB reads only rules linked to this job.
  Executes SELECT checks on UC Delta tables.
  Z-score, volume, freshness, null-rate, behavioral patterns.
  Anomaly events written to DIGITAL_DATA_ANOMALIES.

  <b>DIAGNOSIS (D2)</b> -- How root cause is found:
  Drift Classifier maps to failure taxonomy.
  Lineage Tracer finds Patient Zero upstream.
  Segment Slicer isolates exact micro-segment.
  Playbook Compiler outputs JSON remediation recipe.

  <b>DEFLECTION (D3)</b> -- How issues are contained:
  Circuit Breaker pauses risky downstream jobs.
  Domain Executor agents retrigger pipelines.
  Verification confirms recovery. DRRI updated.
  Notifications sent (P1 Jira + email for CRITICAL).

  <b>BUSINESS OUTCOMES (DRRI >95%)</b>
  MTTD: 48h -> 4h  |  MTTR: 4-8h -> 44min
  40% toil reduction  |  SLA 60% -> 80-88% target
  Measured via check_execution_log + DIGITAL_DATA_ANOMALIES
end note

@enduml
